Jim:	I realize how small Earth is when you look at it from afar. My calling is to realize the truth about life, and this like any experiment must begin from afar, in order to get an objective scientific collection of data, according to the Heisenberg principle, the uncertainty in the measurable quantities to the jolt-like disturbance triggered by the act of observation. Thus, you always contaminate the experiment, therefore must use as little interference as possible, taking into account that those photons transferring the information, have altered the source.
