Jim:	 Notice how you are breathing. Ops – now just by noticing – you already changed your breathing pattern. Just to say, I'm reaching a point where my purpose is no longer foggy and it is only I who can follow my heart's voices to pursue my goals. I will become the first Kualla astronaut and devote my life to research of space. 
No! Stop! I will not allow these winds around to persuade me otherwise. The only one who can discourage me is me myself and I, and one should never underestimate the power of resistance to self realization. One hears about the writer's block, asking what is it that actually stops the creative process, and in most studies it has been demonstrated that the artist is the cause and no surrounding alternation would bring back any productive state. I too must catch my train. It just as well might be my last. 
